\alpha
\vec{r}
\vec{r}+\vec{h}
\nabla \cdot \vec{h}
\vec{r}+\vec{h}=\alpha\vec{r}
\nabla
\nabla \cdot (\vec{r}+\vec{h})=\alpha \nabla \cdot \vec{r}\implies \nabla \cdot \vec{r} + \nabla \cdot \vec{h} = \alpha(\nabla \cdot \vec{r})
\nabla \cdot \vec{r}=3
\nabla \cdot \vec{h}=3(\alpha - 1)
\frac{V_{\text{new}}}{V_{\text{old}}}=\frac{\iiint_{V}\nabla\cdot\vec{h}\:\mathrm{d}V}{\iiint_{V}\:\mathrm{d}V}=3(\alpha - 1)
\frac{V_{\text{new}}}{V_{\text{old}}} \in \mathcal{O}(\alpha^{3})
\frac{a^{3}V_{\text{old}}-V_{\text{old}}}{V_{\text{old}}}=a^{3}-1
a^{3}-1=(1+(a-1))^3-1
(1+x)^{n}=1+nx+\mathcal{O}(x^{2})
a^{3}-1=1+3(a-1)+\mathcal{O}(a-1)^{2}-1=3(a-1)+\mathcal{O}(a-1)^{2}
a \approx 1
a^{3}-1\approx 3(a-1)
